  "description": "<section id=\"description\">\n<p>In English, words like <code>sometimes,</code> <code>always,</code> and <code>never</code> are used to describe the frequency of an action.</p>\n<p><code>Sometimes</code> is used when an action happens on certain occasions but not every time. For example, <code>I sometimes have coffee for breakfast.</code> It indicates possibility but not certainty.</p>\n<p><code>Always</code> is used when an action happens every single time without fail. For instance, <code>The sun always rises in the east.</code> It shows a consistent or habitual action.</p>\n<p><code>Never</code> means an action does not happen at any time. For example, <code>She never eats meat</code>, indicating a complete absence of the action.</p>\n</section>",
